---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — One Run">
  <Nav />
  <section style="padding:160px 48px 80px;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="section-tag">Legal</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:32px;">Privacy <em>Policy</em></h2>
    <div style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.9;color:rgba(243,239,232,0.65);">
      <p style="margin-bottom:24px;">Last updated: May 2026. One Run (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo;, or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) is committed to protecting your personal data. This policy explains how we collect, use, store, and safeguard your information in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">Data we collect</h3>
      <p>When you make a booking or submit an enquiry through our website, we collect the following personal data: full name, email address, phone number, nationality, date of birth, gender (optional), emergency contact name and phone number, medical information relevant to race participation, and payment details. We also collect technical data automatically when you visit our site, including your IP address, browser type, and pages visited, through essential cookies only.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">How we use your data</h3>
      <p>We use your personal data to: process and confirm your booking, communicate with you about your race package, share necessary information with race organizers and hotel partners (name, date of birth, nationality, and medical details where required for race safety), comply with legal obligations including tax and accounting requirements, and send you relevant updates about your booking. We do not use your data for marketing purposes without your explicit consent.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">Data storage and security</h3>
      <p>Your data is stored on secure servers within the European Economic Area (EEA). We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Payment information is processed through Alpha Bank and is not stored on our systems. We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by applicable law (typically 7 years for financial records).</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">Your rights</h3>
      <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights: the right to access the personal data we hold about you, the right to request correction of inaccurate data, the right to request deletion of your data (&ldquo;right to be forgotten&rdquo;), the right to restrict or object to processing of your data, the right to data portability, and the right to withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@one-run.net" style="color:var(--accent);">info@one-run.net</a>. We will respond to your request within 30 days.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:500;color:#f3efe8;margin:32px 0 16px;">Third-party sharing</h3>
      <p>We share your personal data with third parties only when necessary to fulfill your booking: race organizers receive your name, date of birth, nationality, and any required medical information; hotel partners receive your name and stay dates; transfer operators receive your name and flight details where applicable. We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data to any third party for their marketing purposes. If you have concerns about how your data is handled, you also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Hellenic Data Protection Authority.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Base>
